  "description_long": "Silver State Schools is a state-chartered credit union serving members in , , established in 1951. As a not-for-profit financial cooperative, credit unions typically offer lower loan rates, higher savings rates, and fewer fees than traditional banks. This credit union carries a low-income designation, meaning it serves predominantly low-income members and may offer special programs like Payday Alternative Loans (PALs) \u2014 small, affordable loans designed to replace predatory payday lending. The credit union operates 11 branch locations. Deposits are federally insured up to $250,000 by the National Credit Union Administration (NCUA).",
